India won the toss and chose to bat first against South Africa in the second One Day International at Boland Park in Paarl on Friday. South Africa, who batted first in the first ODI on Wednesday, lead the three-match series 1-0 after winning that game. Temba Bavuma and Rassie van der Dussen hit centuries to help their side go one up. The third and final ODI will be played at Newlands in Cape Town on Sunday. South Africa have made one change to their team, bringing in bowler Sisanda Magala for Marco Jansen. India, meanwhile, are unchanged from the first ODI.